# Spinner

An indeterminate loading indicator for pending states.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  spinner.icon([attribute.class("size-5 text-muted-foreground")])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add spinner
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  spinner.icon([])
}
```

## Examples

Size the spinner with utility classes or compose it into other components to signal pending work.

### Sizes

Override the default size with any size utility.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  element.fragment([
    spinner.icon([attribute.class("size-3")]),
    spinner.icon([attribute.class("size-5")]),
    spinner.icon([attribute.class("size-7")]),
    spinner.icon([attribute.class("size-9")]),
  ])
}
```

### Label

Pair the spinner with a short text label when the wait needs context.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  html.div(
    [
      attribute.class(
        "inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground",
      ),
    ],
    [spinner.icon([]), html.text("Loading…")],
  )
}
```

### Button

Add a spinner as a button child and set aria-busy to reveal it. Pair with disabled to block interaction.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  button.button([attribute.aria_busy(True), attribute.disabled(True)], [
    spinner.icon([]),
    html.text("Saving"),
  ])
}
```

### Empty

Fill an empty state's icon slot with the spinner to mark a whole surface as loading.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/empty
import ui/spinner

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  empty.root([], [
    empty.header([], [
      empty.icon([], [spinner.icon([])]),
      empty.title([], [html.text("Processing your request")]),
      empty.description([], [
        html.text("Please wait while we sync your workspace."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Elements

One element, no children. Adjust size, color, and positioning with utility classes.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `spinner.icon(attrs)` | The spinning loader icon. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the spinner's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="spinner"]` | The spinner root. |

## Accessibility

**Decorative by default.** Renders as an aria-hidden icon, a purely visual cue that screen readers skip. Wrapping the spinner and a short text label in a container with role="status" announces the wait politely, once, when the region appears. The spin honors prefers-reduced-motion, slowing to one rotation every six seconds.

